close_reason: "Implemented pm contracts --summary with SDK/MCP contracts, docs, tests, 100% coverage, and packed-install proof."
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/442\n\n## Problem\n`pm contracts` is the machine-discovery entrypoint but costs ~25 KB default JSON (--availability-only is 24.7 KB and still expands every extension/package subcommand); --action create is 63.5 KB; --full is 520 KB. No minimal \"command + one-line intent\" surface exists; agents pay ~25 KB before their first real command.\n\n## Proposed fix\n`pm contracts --summary` emitting one `{ command, intent }` line per top-level command (collapse subcommands/aliases), targeting 1-3 KB; make --availability-only actually lean. Progressive disclosure: summary -> `--command <c> --flags-only` -> --full.\n\n## Relationship\nFeeds epic pm-n7rr acceptance (contracts payload measurably reduced). pm-a22j baselines the numbers; pm-e2bq applies the same tiering to help output. This item is the contracts-side tier.\n\n## Definition of done\n--summary mode sized 1-3 KB in this workspace; --availability-only no longer expands subcommands; sizes recorded before/after on pm-a22j; contracts spec + docs updated."
